The Banū Mūsā brothers (“Sons of Mūsā”) were three 9th-century Persian scholars, of Baghdad, active in the House of Wisdom:
* _Abu Ja'far Muhammad ibn Mūsā ibn Shākir_ (before 803&ndash;873), who specialised in astronomy, engineering, geometry and physics;
* _Ahmad ibn Mūsā ibn Shākir_ (803&ndash;873), who specialised in engineering and mechanics;
* _Al-Hasan ibn Mūsā ibn Shākir_ (810&ndash;873), who specialised in engineering and geometry.
